BOBES_PIERRE@delphi.com writes:
> 1)discover the length of the key by counting coincidences.
> 2)Once that is done shift the key that length and xor it with itself.
> This removes the key and leaves you with test XORed with itself.

This sounds like it was quoted from Bruce Schneier's new book. There is
an error in step 2, it should read, XOR the ciphertext with itself
shifted by the key length.

Other than that, the passage in question explains the process clearly.

Chris Palmer
